<h2 id="description">Description</h2>

<hr />

<font size="4">The hepatitis delta virus (HDV) ribozyme is a non-coding RNA found in the hepatitis delta virus that is necessary for viral replication. It is the only known human virus that utilizes ribozyme activity to infect its host. The ribozyme acts to process the RNA transcripts to unit lengths in a self-cleavage reaction during replication of the hepatitis delta virus, which is thought to propagate by a double rolling circle mechanism. The ribozyme is active in vivo without any protein factors and was the fastest known naturally occurring self-cleaving RNA at the time of its discovery.</font>
<p><br /></p>

